dspace.title: DataSpace: Create the new community "Electrical Engineering"

comments.body:
This needed to be resolved with the inclusion of the following:

```
#!/usr/bin/env jruby
require "highline/import"
require "cli"

netid = 'monikam';
name = ask "Collection Name ";
name = name.strip;

require 'dspace'
DSpace.load()
DSpace.login netid

# This is the root collection for all Library Collections
parent_coll = DSpace.fromString('88435/dsp01g732d9019')
template_coll  = DSpace.fromString('88435/dsp018c97kq48z')

puts "Name:\n\t#{name}";
puts "Template Colection:\n\t#{template_coll.getName}\n\tin #{template_coll.getParentObject().getName}";
yes = ask "do you want to create ? [Y/N] "
if (yes[0] == 'Y') then
    options =  {
        netid: netid,
        template_coll: template_coll.getHandle(),
        parent_handle: parent_coll.getHandle(),
        name: name
    };
    puts ["\tTEMPLATE",template_coll].join "\t"
    new_col = DSpace.create(template_coll).copy(name, parent_coll)
    DSpace.commit
    puts "Committed #{new_col.getHandle()}"
    puts "If restricted access: set 'DEFAULT_BITSTREAM_READ' to Princetion_IPs"
    puts 'add to input-forms'
    puts '   <name-map collection-handle="' + new_col.getHandle + '" form-name="digpubs_serials"/>'

end
```
(ruby/cli/princeton_library/create_top_collection.rb)

...which becomes accessible from the following script:
```
#!/bin/bash
cd ~/ruby/cli
jr_dspace princeton_library/create_top_collection.rb
```
(princeton_library/create_top_collection)
This should be closed once I am able to author a pull request against https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-cli

dspace.title: Please release content listed in the attached spreadsheet from the OAR this Monday (10/28)

comments.body:
In order to complete this task, I needed to invoke the following command, using the title from each item in order to find and release the deposit:

```
$DSPACE_HOME/bin/dspace dsrun edu.princeton.oar.Archive -e symplectic --workflow_state reviewed --new_workflow_state archived_without_email --provenance_msg 'archived_without_email' --verbose --select dc.title --value ...
```

Please be aware that, for some of the items, there is an inconsistency between the casing in the DSpace item metadata, and in the metadata for the records within Symplectic Elements.
